    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860C.01/4–2445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The British Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Churchill</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to President <persName type="to"
                            >Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-24">April 24,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. I have carefully considered message you have handed to Molotov for Marshal
                        Stalin<note n="86" xml:id="d198fn86">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_258">p. 258</ref>.</note> and
                    have brought it before the War Cabinet who have authorized me to inform you of
                    their entire agreement to the course that you have adopted. I shall now
                    therefore send to Marshal Stalin message contained in my immediately following
                        telegram.<note n="87" xml:id="d198fn87">Telegram No. 15, April 24, not
                        printed. For text of Prime Minister Churchii’s message of April 24 to
                        Marshal Stalin, see Churchill, <hi rend="italic">Triumph and Tragedy</hi>,
                        p. 492.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
